<p>but very little quarter was given &amp; none asked for, they were shot as fast as they came out.</p>
<p>About 10 oclock a stand to was ordered for we could see Germans in the distance massing for a counter attack but our guns promptly took all that out of their heads, about 60 of them reached the fringe of the wood, &amp; there they were scattered by our machine gun &amp; rifle fire you should have seen the boys standing up &amp; shouting to the oncoming German's urging them on &amp; promising them something when they reached our trenches, which happily for them they did not do we got all these men later in</p>
